divs: Sighting Details Woke up a little after 4am to smoke a cigg. like i normally do around that time and looked up in the sky to see a moving star. I didnt see any flashing lights and it was really quite. So I continued to watch as it seemed real close to the ground to be a star? Anyway it continued North East kinda slow and fast, sometimes it would dim and then get bright. I lost it over time cause of the trees but it was definitly not anything I've ever seen. As I was watching that one I noticed a larger star like object, also too close to the ground to be a star just hovering over like St. Paul, it was doing the same dim then get bright but it never moved so i went back to sleep, tried too anyway.
Summary: Moving slow in a sort of zig-zag motion and it was real quite
